## Methodology

### 1. Material Selection
Selected 2×2 twill woven CFRP face sheets with PVC foam 
core based on specific stiffness, manufacturability, and 
regulatory compliance criteria.

### 2. Concept Design
Three concepts evaluated using weighted decision matrix:
- Manufacturability: 25%
- Regulatory compliance: 20%
- Mass: 15%
- Flat-Top Minimal concept selected with score 73/100

### 3. ANSYS ACP Simulation
Full composite laminate model built in ANSYS ACP — 
individual ply orientations, thickness distributions, 
and failure criteria defined. Three-point bending 
simulation performed under identical boundary conditions 
to physical test.

### 4. VARI Manufacturing
Physical test specimens manufactured using Vacuum Assisted 
Resin Infusion (VARI) process — dry lay-up, vacuum bagging, 
resin infusion, and cure.

### 5. Physical Test Validation
Specimens tested under three-point bending — experimental 
results correlated with ANSYS ACP simulation confirming 
shear-dominated core failure mode and face-to-core load 
transfer behaviour.

